    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>The Plan &amp;c came safely.<note type="editorial">In his previous letter,
                        Pennant requested a small plan of the Forth and Clyde canal, then under
                        construction. Available plans included <bibl type="editorial">John Smeaton's
                            <title ref="bi0641"><hi rend="italic">A General Map of the Country betwixt
                                    the Forth &amp; Clyde extracted from a map of Sterling Shire
                                    &amp;c by William Edgar 1745, shewing the Course of the intended
                                    canals. Engraved by Andrew Bell</hi></title>,
                        1764</bibl>.</note> I imagine myself amply supplied with materials for
                    <placeName ref="pl0371">Dumferline</placeName> many thanks for all favors past
                    &amp; promised. Before the box is packed up pray ask <persName ref="pe0022">Doctor
                        Ramsay</persName> for certain shells &amp;c. I do not care two pence ab<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> any cardinals Bastard.<note type="editorial">Probably a reference to <persName ref="pe0063">Cardinal David
                            Beaton</persName>: see Paton's letter to Pennant on 4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> April 1775.</note> I rejoice to hear of the
                    new works especially <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0159">Lord
                            Hails</title></bibl>. Be so good as to forward the inclosed. <persName ref="pe0158">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Macintyre</persName> will be at
                        y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Gen. assembly.</p>
                <closer><salute>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> most obedt</salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">T.P.</persName></signed>
                <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName>. May 5<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1775.</dateline></closer>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom House</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Edinburgh</addrLine>
                    </address></p>
            </div>
        </body>
